U.S. drilling activity rose last weekwith the number of working rotary rigs up by 23 to 784, against1,063 working rigs one year ago, Hughes Tool Co. said.    The improvement was the first increase this year in theweekly rig count, which had dropped steadily since earlyJanuary when a total of 962 rotary rigs were working.    Among individual states, Texas and Oklahoma reported thebiggest gains in drilling last week with increases of 21 and11, respectively. California and Louisiana were each up bythree and Wyoming gained two additional working rigs.    Hughes Tool said it counted a total of 692 rigs drilling onland, 74 rigs active offshore and 18 drilling in inland waters.In Canada, the rig count was up by two to 183, against 324 oneyear ago. Reuter&#3;